05/11/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Interior Minister Hari Kostov met with EU security chief Javier Solana in Brussels on Tuesday (4 November) to discuss the EU police mission in Macedonia, Proxima, which will succeed the military mission, Concordia, on 15 December. They also discussed regional security and Macedonia's ongoing campaign to collect illegal weapons.
In other news Tuesday, a Macedonian delegation presented the country's Membership Action Plan for 2003-2004 to NATO representatives in Brussels. Alliance officials in turn urged Skopje to speed up reforms. (MIA, A1 TV - 04/11/03)
